# The Spice Melange · the substance that binds the universe

The spice melange is the most precious substance in the universe, and it is found in only one place: the desert world of Arrakis. It is produced in the deep desert through the life-cycle of the sandworms, drawn up out of the sand by the great work of those creatures. There is no other source. To possess Arrakis is to possess the spice, and to possess the spice is to hold the single thread on which the whole Imperium hangs.

What the melange gives is not wealth alone but transformation. It extends life. It expands consciousness. And in the Guild Navigators it kindles the limited prescience by which they fold space and move the ships of the Imperium safely between the stars. Through this gift the spice binds every house, every power, every world into a common dependence — for without it the great web of travel and rule would come apart. It is the prize every power kills for.

The melange belongs to the cosmology of Dune, the unseen weave on which the order of the universe is strung. Its nature of emergence is ethereal because its true power lies beyond the embodied: prescience and the folding of space, the expansion of mind, the binding of an empire by a thing that cannot be seen so much as felt and foreseen. He who controls the spice controls the universe — and because he who can destroy a thing controls it, the substance that binds all things is also the lever by which all things may be moved.
